  "prompt": "Is there any way to insert image/picture in nedit text editor?",
  "response": "No, **NEdit** (Nirvana Editor) is a **plain text editor** and does not support the insertion or display of images or pictures. It is specifically designed for editing plain text files, such as source code, configuration files, or other text-based documents. If you need to work with images or other rich media, you would need to use a different editor or tool, such as:\n\n1. **LibreOffice Writer** or **Microsoft Word** for rich text documents with embedded images.\n2. **Markdown editors** (e.g., Typora or Visual Studio Code with Markdown preview) for documents where images are referenced via links.\n3. **HTML editors** if you\u2019re working with web content and need to embed images.\n\nFor plain text files, you can always reference an image file by its path or URL, but the image itself won\u2019t be displayed within NEdit.",
